content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: --SPCUFL
      operator: non_empty
    - name: --SPCUFL
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: N
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.182
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: Raise an error when record is --SPCUFL is not null and is not equal to
  'N'
Outcome:
  Message: --SPCUFL must be 'N' or null.
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '182'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: -SPCUFL describes the usability of the specimen for
                  the test. Example, N = the specimen is not usable; otherwise null.
                Document: SENDIG v3.1
                Section: Section 6.3.6
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - FINDINGS
  Domains:
    Include:
      - LB
      - MA
      - MI
      - PC
